        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Troops Before Politicians Act&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill withholds the pay of Members of Congress if active service members of the Armed Forces are not receiving pay, including as a result of a lapse in appropriations (i.e., a government shutdown). The withheld pay of Members must be deposited into an escrow account and released when the military lapse in pay ends.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
